text.tspan: In the cellar, pots of yeast, blankets,
some extra clothes, and the owners
The front room is a taylors shop
with an old man ineptly doing
needlework. He points to the right
and locks the door if any pass into
Big room in the back has a chest
out and watch the doors. Secret
door to the sewers in the back.
A magic mouth greets visitors and asks
their name and business. The first floor is
the command of the magic mouth. Top
floor also houses a talking, mean crocodile
1. Krah, a one legged tengu hiring guards (HD 4)
2. Zara, well armed woman wanting to start a gang (F4)
3. Mogblob, a grumbling troll trying to fit in (HD 4)
4. lvig, a singing huldra looking for a man (HD 3)
5. Isssht, a quiet serpent man in metal armor (F4)
6. Fiona, a sorceress entertaining the guests (M3)
1. simple elven sword +1 with the emblems of
a house now extinct (did they own land?)
2. bane cards that stun anybody who sees
one up close; every use has a 5% chance
3. tome of aquatic anatomy which teaches
the grafting of shark gills to another being;
4. poseidons trident, grants ability to speak
with sea born creatures at will and
5. ring of djinn mastery, grants permanent
control over an invisible servant, flies,
carries up to 5 lb., fades for a minute if hit;
bestows enmity of all elemental creatures
6. bracers of the snake, grants Dex 18; broad-
casts your actions to all servants of Set
Starting a fight in the bakery
attracts a lot of hungry looters
armed with clubs (F1). They use flour
to blind intruders (-4), save to avoid.
Miracles: light, light cure, detect magic, paralyze person, silence, living weapon (+1d6)
Spells: light, charm object (HD 2), read thoughts, magic mouth, thunderbolt (5d6)
Abbreviations: Cleric, Dwarf, Elf, Fighter, Halfling, Mage, Thief, Hit Dice.
